title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1987-09-19
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC 2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half-Step, Uptown Toodeloo, It's All Over Now, High Time, Mexicali Blues > Big River, When Push Comes To Shove, Box Of Rain > Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Crazy Fingers > Uncle John's Band > Playing In The Band > Drums > Space > I Need A Miracle > Maggie's Farm > Black Peter > Around & Around > Turn On Your Love Light Encore: Black Muddy River

TV Broadcast for Farm Aid

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text:
incomplete Dunno why, but Space cuts off with a minute to go and Miracle is missing completely.  The fileset at etree is complete, so maybe it was a problem with the upload here?

Musically, this show is outstanding and this sbd source sounds excellent.  If you don't know, this is one of the major Playing in the Bands from the era, but the whole 2nd set is primo.
